com.github.basking2.sdsai.dsds.node.tx

Class TransactionalNodeStore<USERKEY,STOREKEY,VALUE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.basking2.sdsai.dsds.node.tx.TransactionalNodeStore<USERKEY,STOREKEY,VALUE>
  • Type Parameters:
    USERKEY - The user key type.
    STOREKEY - The data store key type.
    VALUE - The value being stored.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    NodeStore<USERKEY,STOREKEY,VALUE>

    public class TransactionalNodeStore<USERKEY,STOREKEY,VALUE>
extends java.lang.Object
implements NodeStore<USERKEY,STOREKEY,VALUE>
    This represents a transaction against a NodeStore. Operations are stored cached internally until commit() is called or rollback() causes the data to be abandoned. A transaction. This is implemented as a NodeStore in which methods not related to the transaction are directly proxied to the NodeStore used to initialize this object.
